      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Real Meaning Of 'Cross at the Green'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Julia Schoeck letter corrects July 23 FYI item about slogan 'cross at the green, not in between' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fighting Chance on Foot'' (F.Y.I., July 23): I believe that the slogan ''Cross at the green, not in between'' was used to promote crossing at the intersection and not in the middle of the block, otherwise known as jaywalking. It had nothing to do with the subject of your report, ''Walk/Don't Walk'' signs.</p>
        <p>JULIA SCHOECK  Douglaston, Queens</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
